subproject.description:
The Project is expected to deliver the following three key outputs: (i) a diagnostic
study known as a Legislative Needs Assessment to assess and document the capacity building
needs of the Olbiil Era Kelulau and its support offices and strategies to address them; (ii) an
Orientation workshop for the Senators and Delegates of Palau; and (iii) the design of a
legislative support package to provide targeted support to the Senators, Delegates and the
legislative support Office including the Offices of the Clerk and Legal Counsel. The Project
design exercise will involve important stakeholders including Legislators, Office of the
President, senior government officials and development partner who will be invited to
participate in one day workshop where the recommendations of the LNA and capacity
assessment report will be jointly discussed, validated and prioritized
